import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Regions', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['income'], data['health'], c=data['region'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Health')
    ax.set_title('How does health vary with income?')
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Regions")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['population'])
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the population distribution across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(['Population'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by region and calculate the mean of income and health
    grouped_data = data.groupby('region')[['income', 'health']].mean().reset_index()

    # Create a grouped bar chart
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    index = grouped_data.index
    bar_width = 0.35
    opacity = 0.8

    rects1 = ax.bar(index, grouped_data['income'], bar_width, alpha=opacity, color='b', label='Income')
    rects2 = ax.bar(index + bar_width, grouped_data['health'], bar_width, alpha=opacity, color='g', label='Health')

    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Values')
    ax.set_title('What is the average income and health of each region?')
    ax.set_xticks(index + bar_width / 2)
    ax.set_xticklabels(grouped_data['region'], rotation=45)
    ax.legend()

    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
